description._content: Description: Some Attractive Visitors from the Country. Miss Gladys Matthews, only daughter of Mr. and Mrs. D. H. Matthews, of Aven Dewns Station, Burren Junction, who is on a visit to Sydney for the bridge festivities. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Some Attractive Visitors from the Country. Mrs. George Clark, of Terramingamine Station, Dubbo, who is enjoying a holiday trip to the city, spending the time between Collarey and Roseville. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Some Attractive Visitors from the Country. Miss Peggy (Struan) Brown, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. G. H. Brown, of Fairfield Station, Boggabri, who is holidaying with her family at Manly. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Some Attractive Visitors from the Country. Miss Belle Fisher, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. A. T. Fisher, of Wilgara Station, Coonambie, who is staying with her friend, Miss Joan Daniel, at Mosnam Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/607. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons.
